A series of shootings in [[Ottawa]], [[Canada]] began shortly before 10:00 [[UTC-4|EDT]] on October 22, 2014, when one gunman shot and killed a [[Canadian Forces]] soldier outside the [[National War Memorial (Canada)|Canadian National War Memorial]] who was on ceremonial guard duty. The gunman then proceeded into the [[Parliament of Canada|Canadian Parliament buildings]], where he was reportedly shot dead by [[Kevin Vickers]], the [[List of Sergeants-at-Arms of the Canadian House of Commons|Sergeant-at-Arms of the Canadian House of Commons]].<ref name="CBC live">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/parliament-hill-attacked-soldier-shot-at-national-war-memorial-in-ottawa-1.2808710|title=Parliament Hill attacked, soldier shot at National War Memorial in Ottawa|date=22 October 2014|publisher=|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref><ref name="G&M breaking">{{cite web|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/breaking-news-oct-22/article21217602/|title=Attack on Ottawa: Police in pursuit of multiple shooters|work=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref>

Subsequent to these initial events, Ottawa's downtown core was put under [[lockdown]], including Canada's Parliament and the [[University of Ottawa]].<ref name="CBC live" /><ref name="G&M breaking" /> The [[Ottawa Police Service]] stated they are investigating three shootings: one at the Canadian National War Memorial, one at [[Parliament Hill]], and one near the [[Rideau Centre]].<ref name="G&M breaking" /> The attack came a day after two Canadian Forces soldiers were struck by an [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] sympathizer in a car, killing one of them, and after Canada raised its terror threat level from low to medium.<ref name="BBC News">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-29724907?ns_mchannel=social&ns_campaign=bbc_breaking&ns_source=twitter&ns_linkname=news_central|title=Shots fired inside Canada parliament|work=BBC News|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref>

The slain solder was a reservist from Hamilton, Ontario and a member of the [[The Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders of Canada (Princess Louise's)|Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders]]. He was taken to hospital and reported by Minister [[Jason Kenney]] as having died. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/hamilton/news/canadian-soldier-shot-in-ottawa-a-reservist-from-hamilton-1.2808960|title=Canadian soldier shot in Ottawa a reservist from Hamilton|date=22 October 2014|publisher=|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref>

